title: What are the names of Bob Dylan's early hits? - Quora

response.answer_text: By early Bob Dylan hits, I am assuming releases from the 60’s. There are only 2, neither of which made it all the way to Number 1. The iconic “Like a Rolling Stone” hit No. 2 on the Billboard Hot 100 back in September 1965, as did “Rainy Day Women #12 and 35” in May 1966. But he’s never reached No. 1 on any individual chart until recently with the weird “Murder Most Foul.” The Bob Dylan penned "Mr. Tambourine Man" single by the Byrds was released in April 1965, reached number one on the Billboard Hot 100. Their second single "All I Really Want to Do", also a Dylan cover, was moderately successful.
